                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the west wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Rājarāja III. Year 2: 1217 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription registers an agreement (<hi rend="italic">ubhayattīṭṭu</hi>) given to Vīrāṇam-uḍaiyāṉ Udaiyaṉ Tiruk[ka]ttuṟaiyuḍaiyān <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Alaṅgārappiriyan, the <hi rend="italic">[ū]ṛkaṇakku</hi> of Peṇṇāgaḍam by three <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> who were in the enjoyment of <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> in the temple of god Tirunāgīśvaram-uḍaiya Nāyaṉār of Tiruppālaippandal to supply the necessary articles (specified) for the worship of the god on <hi rend="italic">śivarātri</hi> day in the month of Māśi with the interest on the 300 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> received from the former in the month of Pūraṭṭādi of the year.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
